Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision systems and image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of attribute labels for content, emotions, and artistic media suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The baseline experiments and study of visual domain adaptation indicate a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of large-scale datasets and annotations suggests an information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
